comments: Wiggins (GSW) extends his right hand outward and marginal contact occurs with Ball's (CHA) front as Ball dribbles inside the perimeter.
Paschall (GSW) ends his dribble and hops consecutively on the same foot after his gather.

Washington (CHA) initiates contact with Paschall's (GSW) right shoulder during his upward shooting motion that affects his layup attempt. The contact occurs prior to Washington making contact with the ball thereafter.
Green (GSW) initiates contact with Rozier's (CHA) right arm and front, affecting Rozier's SQBR along the perimeter.
Rozier (CHA) and Oubre Jr. (GSW) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Bridges (CHA) establishes himself in a screening position in Oubre Jr.'s (GSW) path and absorbs the contact.
Wiggins (GSW) and Hayward (CHA) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Washington (CHA) maintains a legal guarding position as contact occurs with Green (GSW) at the top of the perimeter. Washington then makes clean contact with the ball as Green is passing.
Washington (CHA) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the body contact made with Wiggins (GSW) at the end of the drive.
Ball (CHA) moves forward to contest the jump shot attempt by Oubre Jr. (GSW) and any contact that occurs as he lands is marginal.
Paschall (GSW) and Hayward (CHA) come together off ball and marginal contact occurs as they separate.
Oubre Jr. (GSW) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Rozier (CHA) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Green (GSW) makes incidental contact with Washington's (CHA) backside as he back-taps the rebound.

Ball (CHA) has a grasp of Wanamaker's (GSW) left arm during rebounding and quickly releases. Ball then swipes his left arm forward in an attempt to back-tap the ball and some contact occurs with Wanamaker's head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Washington (CHA) is moving forward as Wanamaker (GSW) turns backward and marginal contact occurs after Wanamaker picks up his dribble.
Ball (CHA) reaches in and cleanly ties Wanamaker (GSW) up. A jump ball is correctly assessed.
Washington (CHA) has a grasp of Green's (GSW) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Green bats the ball forward following the jump ball.

Green (GSW) and Wiggins (GSW) make incidental contact with Hayward (CHA) after Hayward gains full control of the ball. Hayward falls to the floor while still maintaining control and CHA signals for the timeout before Green makes contact with the ball. CHA is then correctly awarded the timeout.
All technical fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
All technical fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Washington (CHA) establishes himself in a screening position in Oubre Jr.'s (GSW) path and absorbs the side-to-side contact.
Rozier (CHA) loses control of the ball after it makes contact with his knee and legally continues his dribble following the loss of control.
Toscano-Anderson (GSW) legally contests Rozier's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
